  "text": "In 1975 Schwartz et al. [CITATION_1] called attention to the presence of a lower than normal heart rate in many patients, a phenomenon particularly striking in children. During exercise, several LQTS patients reach a heart rate level lower than that achieved by healthy controls matched by age and sex.",
